description: As the possibility of an IDF invasion into Rafah looms, the pressure for Hamas to agree to a hostage release deal is rising, says Amb. Dennis Ross. He joins Meet the Press NOW to discuss the latest cease-fire proposal that's on the table.
title: Looming Israeli offensive increases pressure on Hamas to agree to cease-fire: Amb. Dennis Ross

description: Dozens of people were killed in western Kenya after the Old Kijabe Dam collapsed following weeks of heavy rains across the country. Flooding also caused a boat carrying several people to capsize in the Tana River in northern Kenya.
title: Kenya dam collapse kills dozens after weeks of heavy rain

description: The members of Haiti's transitional presidential council are under pressure to bring stability to the country quickly, despite a humanitarian crisis that has been years in the making.
title: New leaders take on Haiti’s chaos as those living in fear demand swift solutions to gang violence

description: Hong Kong transgender activist Henry Tse received a new ID card reflecting his gender change, after a yearslong legal battle to change the document.
title: Hong Kong transgender activist gets ID card reflecting gender change after yearslong legal battle

description: NATO Secretary General Jens Stoltenberg said during a visit to Kyiv that the situation on the Ukrainian battlefield depends on the speediness of military aid to Ukraine.
title: NATO chief Stoltenberg urges speedy military aid for Ukraine

description: Scotland’s first minister, Humza Yousaf, resigned on Monday rather than face a no-confidence vote just days after he torpedoed a coalition with the Green Party by ditching a target for fighting climate change.
title: Scotland’s leader resigns, adding to U.K. political turmoil

description: Ukraine’s outnumbered troops have been forced to retreat from three villages on the eastern front lines, the country’s top commander said Sunday, as Russian forces push to break through its beleaguered defenses while Kyiv waits for newly-committed U.S. military aid to arrive.
title: Ukraine retreats in the east as Russia pushes forward while U.S. ally waits for aid

description: Students in Rafah, Gaza, protested for an end to the Israel-Hamas war and for education protection that was interrupted due to war. An NBC News crew in Gaza interviewed a student on why she's protesting.
title: Students in Gaza protest against the war and for education protection
